A senior Korean Air executive who exploded in a rage at a flight attendant after her peanuts were served in a bag instead of on a dish has today been charged over the incident.

Furious Cho Hyun-ah, a senior vice-president at the airline, angrily demanded the removal of a crew member from a flight for failing to serve her macadamia nuts in the correct way. 

She has now been charged with 'threatening the plane's safety' and could spend up to 15 years in prison if found guilty of the four charges she faces.

