South Korean media branded the 40-year-old a princess and while others branded her an embarrassment to her country.

Cho's behavior caused uproar in the country and the airline's defense of her and its attempt to blame the crew member prompted even more criticism.

The incident touched a nerve in a country where the economy is dominated by family-run conglomerates known as 'chaebol' that often act above the law.

